            "subject": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Don't call lnet_finalize in IRQ"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Ian Ziemba",
          "email": "ian.ziemba@hpe.com",
          "date": "2021-06-18 18:20:15.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Chris Horn",
          "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
          "date": "2022-07-27 15:15:06.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Use KFI_TAGGED_RMA capabilites",
        "message": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Use KFI_TAGGED_RMA capabilites\n\nKFI_TAGGED_RMA allows for RMA read/write operations to target a tagged\nreceive buffer instead of target memory region. By using\nKFI_TAGGED_RMA with kfilnd, all target memory registration can be\navoided. Avoiding memory registration with the kCXI provider results\nin at least a 2x bandwidth and RPC/s increase for LST 4K read/write\noperations.\n\nSince kfilnd no longer requires target memory registration, all memory\nregistration code is removed. This includes the usage of kfi event\nqueues since these event queues were only used to report memory\nregistration events.\n\nThe kfilnd transaction state machine has been update to reflect the\nusage of KFI_TAGGED_RMA. This includes updating all the debugfs\ntransaction statistics to report duration for the new states.\n\nAll these changes were tested with the kfilnd defined CFS fail\nlocation values and LST.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-10119\nSigned-off-by: Ian Ziemba <ian.ziemba@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: I682bb29ac4c65bfaf93fed7ae002da0945d02daa\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
